      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Peradeniya ¶ Ceylon ¶ 4th March 1870 ¶ My dear Hooker ¶ [Discusses botanical matters]...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">M70.03.04</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From George Thwaites to Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Directors' correspondence, vol. 162, ff 393-4</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Peradeniya</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Ceylon</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">4th March 1870</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Hooker</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">[Discusses botanical matters]</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">…</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I heard from Moore of Sydney that, though v. Mueller continues the nominal Director of the Melbourne Garden, a Mr. Ferguson is virtually the Director having charge of the work in it, and that von Mueller is now really only the Government Botanist, and that he is in low spirits about it. I wrote some time ago congratulating v. Mueller upon being relieved from the mere garden duties,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
               </note> thinking it would be a pleasant arrangement for him and not expecting it would have annoyed him. It makes one fear that his love of science does not sufficiently predominate over his appetite for κυδος<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>kudos. </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">…</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">[Discusses botanical matters and field trips]</p>
         </div>
